Set Up the Preview in a Recipe
A recipe displays a preview of your data on the Preview tab as you work. You can set the columns and number of rows that appear in this preview.
If needed, manually add multivalue fields to the recipe.
If working with a connected object over 10,000 rows, CRM Analytics loads a sample of 10,000 rows into the recipe.
Use filters only on sample data, not on updated samples.
The preview shows null values as “null” in gray italics and empty strings as blank values.
Hide columns from the column menu if not needed.
Click the columns tab to work with numerous columns without data.
All recipe columns appear first, color-coded by source, with their type, dataset, and missing values indicator.
To find a column, start typing its name in the search box.
To hide or add back a column, select from its menu.
The recipe preview can display up to 100 fields. If removed, it’s not included in the target dataset unless reselected when creating the dataset.
title: Setting Up Recipe Preview in CRM Analytics
